cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with temporal logics and their algebraic characterization. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a likely category as the paper discusses forest automata and their relationship with forest languages. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with ordered tuples of trees, which can be seen as a data structure. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses automata and their recognition of languages, which can be related to machine learning. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper deals with the definability problem of a logic fragment.
